      section
        h2 Working with your Microsoft Account and OneDrive
        hr
        ul
            li Many of the new features in Office 2013 are geared towards saving and sharing files online. 
            li To use these features, you'll need to get a free Microsoft account (previously called a Windows Live ID) if you don't already have one. 
            li You can then log in to your Microsoft account to access your OneDrive which is an online storage space for your documents and other files.

