      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          h1 Find and Replace
          li When you're working with longer presentations, it can be difficult and time consuming to locate a specific word or phrase. PowerPoint can automatically search your presentation using the Find feature, and it allows you to quickly change words or phrases using the Replace feature.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          h2 To find text:
          li In our example, we'll use the Find feature to look for specific dog breeds in our presentation.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li From the Home tab, click the Find command.
          img(src="images/text/find1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li A dialog box will appear. Enter the text you wish to find in the Find what: field, then click Find Next.
          img(src="images/text/find2.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li If the text is found, it will be selected.
          img(src="images/text/find3.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li Click Find Next to find further instances. If none are found, a dialog box will appear. Click OK.
          img(src="images/text/find4.png")
          li When you are finished, click Close to exit the dialog box.
          li You can also access the Find command by pressing Ctrl+F on your keyboard.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          h2 To replace text:
          li At times, you may discover that you've repeatedly made a mistake throughout your presentation (such as misspelling someone's name), or that you need to exchange a particular word or phrase for another. You can use the Replace feature to make quick revisions. In our example, we'll replace with word "pounds" with the abbreviation "lbs."

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li From the Home tab, click the Replace command.
          img(src="images/text/find5.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li A dialog box will appear. Type the text you wish to find in the Find what: field.
          li Type the text you wish to replace it with in the Replace with: field, then click Find Next.
          img(src="images/text/find6.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li If the text is found, it will be selected. Review the text to make sure you want to replace it.
          li If you wish to replace it, select one of the replace options. Replace will replace individual instances, and Replace All will replace every instance. In our example, we'll use the Replace option.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          img(src="images/text/find7.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li The selected text will be replaced.
          img(src="images/text/find8.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li You'll need to be careful when using the Replace All option. In the example below, changing the word "Pounds" to "lbs." would have been incorrect in this context. You can click Find Next to skip to the next instance without replacing the text.
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
       
          li If you're using a theme, you'll probably find that your presentation looks pretty good. All of the colors will work well together, which means you won't have to spend as much time formatting your presentation. But there's another great reason to use theme elements: When you switch to a different theme, all of those elements will update to reflect the new theme. You can drastically change the look of your presentation in a few clicks.

