        h2 About slide views
          li PowerPoint includes several different slide views, which are all useful for various tasks. The slide view commands are located in the bottom-right of the PowerPoint window. There are four main slide views:
          img(src="images/manage/manage1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Normal view: This is the default view, where you create and edit slides. You can also move slides in the slide navigation pane on the left.
        img(src="images/manage/manage2.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Slide sorter: In this view, you'll see a thumbnail version of each slide. You can drag and drop slides to reorder them quickly.
        img(src="images/manage/manage3.jpg")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Reading view: This view fills the PowerPoint window with a preview of your presentation. It includes easily accessible navigation buttons at the bottom-right.
        img(src="images/manage/manage4.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Play slide show: This is the view you'll use to present to an audience. This command will begin the presentation from the current slide. You can also press F5 on your keyboard to start from the beginning.
        img(src="images/manage/manage5.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Outline View
        li Outline View shows your slide text in outline form. This allows you to quickly edit your slide text and view the content of multiple slides at once. You could use this layout to review the organization of your slide show and prepare to deliver your presentation.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
