          h2 Slide Master View
          h3 What is Slide Master view?

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         p Slide Master view is a special feature in PowerPoint that allows you to quickly modify the slides and slide layouts in your presentation. From there, you can edit the slide master, which will affect every slide in the presentation. You can also modify individual slide layouts, which will change any slides using those layouts.

         p For example, let's say you find a theme you like but you don't like the slide layouts. You could use Slide Master view to customize the layouts exactly the way you want them to look.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 Using Slide Master view
         p Whether you're making significant changes to your slides or just a few small tweaks, Slide Master view can help you create a consistent, professional presentation without a lot of effort. You could use Slide Master view to change just about anything in your presentation, but here are some of its most common uses:

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Modify backgrounds: Slide Master view makes it easy to customize the background for all of your slides at the same time. For example, you could add a watermark or logo to each slide in your presentation, or you could modify the background graphics of an existing PowerPoint theme.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Rearrange placeholders: If you find that you often rearrange the placeholders on each slide, you can save time by rearranging them in Slide Master view instead. When you adjust one of the layouts in Slide Master view, all of the slides with that layout will change.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Customize text formatting: Rather than changing the text color on each slide individually, you could use the Slide Master to change the text color on all slides at once.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Create unique slide layouts: If you want to create a presentation that looks distinct from regular PowerPoint themes, you could use Slide Master view to create your own layouts. Custom layouts can include your own background graphics, and placeholders.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To make changes to all slides:
         p If you want to change something on all slides of your presentation, you can edit the Slide Master. In our example, we'll add a logo to every slide.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select the View tab, then click the Slide Master command. 
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_command.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li The presentation will switch to Slide Master view, and the Slide Master tab will be selected on the Ribbon.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li In the left navigation pane, scroll up and select the first slide. This is the slide master.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_select.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Use the desired tabs on the Ribbon to make changes to the Slide Master. In our example, we’ll insert a picture in the upper-left corner of the slide.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_insert_picture.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Move, resize, or delete other slide objects as needed. In our example, we'll resize the background graphic to fit below our newly inserted logo.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_resize.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li When you’re finished, click the Close Master View command on the Slide Master tab.
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_close.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li The change will appear on all slides of the presentation.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_done.jpeg")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         p When you make a change to the Slide Master, it's a good idea to review your presentation to see how it affects each slide. You may find that some of your slides don't look exactly right. On the next page, we'll show you how to fix this by customizing individual slide layouts.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 Customizing slide layouts

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         p You can use Slide Master view to modify any slide layout in your presentation. It's easy to make small tweaks like adjusting background graphics and more significant changes like rearranging or deleting placeholders. Unlike the Slide Master, changes to a slide layout will only be applied to slides using that layout in your presentation.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To customize an existing slide layout:
         p In our example, our newly added logo overlaps a background graphic in the Content with Caption Layout. We'll customize this layout to make room for the logo.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Navigate to Slide Master view.
         li Locate and select the desired layout in the left navigation pane. You can hover the mouse over each layout to see which slides are currently using that layout in the presentation.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_exist_select.png")


       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li In some layouts, the background graphics may be hidden. To show the graphics, uncheck the box next to Hide Background Graphics.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_layout_hide.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Add, move, or delete any objects as desired. In our example, we'll move the red arrow to better show our new logo.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_move_arrow.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li If you want to change the arrangement of the placeholders, you can move, resize, or delete any of them. In our example, we'll move our placeholders down to align with the red arrow.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_move_placeholder.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li When you're finished, click the Close Master View command on the Slide Master tab.
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_all_close.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li All slides using the layout will be updated.
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_move_compare.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 Customizing text formatting
         p You can also customize the text formatting from Slide Master view, including the font, text size, color, and alignment. For example, if you wanted to change the font for every title placeholder in your presentation, you could modify the master title style on the Slide Master.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
