         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_custom_command.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li A new slide layout will appear.
         li The layout will include Title and Footer placeholders by default. Click the Title and Footers boxes in the Master Layout group to toggle these placeholders on and off.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_custom_new_title2.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click the bottom half of the Insert Placeholder command, then select the desired placeholder type. We recommend using the Content placeholder most of the time because it can be used for any type of slide content.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_custom_placeholder.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click and drag to draw the placeholder on the slide. You can add more placeholders if desired.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/slidemaster/master_custom_draw.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Using the other tabs on the Ribbon, you can also add background graphics, shapes, or pictures to the slide layout.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To rename a custom layout:
         p You'll want to give your custom layout a unique name so it will be easy to find.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Navigate to Slide Master view.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
