        h2 Rehearsing slide show timings
        li Rehearsing timings can be useful if you want to set up a presentation to play at a certain speed without having to click through the slides to present it. Think of it as a tool to help you practice presenting your slide show. Using this feature, you can save timings for each slide and animation. PowerPoint will then play back the presentation with the same timings when you present it.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To rehearse timings:
        li Select the Slide Show tab, then locate the Set Up group.
        li Click the Rehearse Timings command. You will be taken to a full-screen view of your presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Practice presenting your slide show. When you are ready to move to the next slide, click the Next button on the Recording Toolbar in the top-left corner. If you prefer, you can also use the right arrow key.
        img(src="images/advance/advance2.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li When you have reached the end of the show, a dialog box will appear with the total time of your presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance3.png")
        li If you are satisfied with your timings, click Yes.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li If you need more than one try to get the timings just right, the Recording Toolbar has options to let you take a break or start over on a slide.
        img(src="images/advance/advance4.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Recording your slide show
        li The Record Slide Show feature is similar to the Rehearse Timings feature, but it's a bit more comprehensive. If you have a microphone for your computer, you can even record voiceover narration for the entire presentation. This is useful if you plan on using your slide show for a self-running presentation or a video

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To record a slide show:
        li Click the Slide Show tab, then locate the Set Up group.
        li Click the Record Slide Show drop-down arrow. Select either Start Recording from Beginning or Start Recording from Current Slide.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/advance/advance5.png")
        li A dialog box will appear. Select the desired options. Remember, you can only record narration if you have a microphone attached to your computer.
        img(src="images/advance/advance6.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Click Start Recording. Your presentation will open to a full screen.
        li Perform your slide show. Make sure to speak clearly into the microphone if you are recording narration. When you are ready to move to the next slide, click the Next button on the Recording Toolbar in the top-left corner or use the right arrow key.
        img(src="images/advance/advance7.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li When you reach the end of the show, PowerPoint will close the full-screen view.
        li Your slide show timings and narration are now included in your presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance8.jpg")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To remove narration or timings from a recorded slide show:
        li Click the Slide Show tab, then locate the Set Up group.
        li Click the Record Slide Show drop-down arrow.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Hover the mouse over Clear, then select the desired option.
        img(src="images/advance/advance10.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 To create a video:
        li Click the File tab to access Backstage view.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Select Export, then click Create a Video. Video export options will appear on the right.
        img(src="images/advance/advance11.jpg")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Click the drop-down arrow next to Computer and HD Displays to select the size and quality of your video.
        img(src="images/advance/advance12.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Select the drop-down arrow next to Use Recorded Timings and Narrations.
        li Choose Don't Use Recorded Timings and Narrations if you don't have or don't wish to use recorded timings. You can adjust the default Seconds to spend on each slide: in the box below the drop-down menu.
        li Choose Use Recorded Timings and Narrations if you have already recorded timings and narrations and would like to use them in your video.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/advance/advance13.png")
        li Click Create Video. The Save As dialog box will appear.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Select the location where you wish to save the presentation, then enter a name for the presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance14.png")
        li Click Save. As PowerPoint creates your video, a status bar will appear at the bottom of the PowerPoint window. When the bar is complete, your video is ready to view, send, or upload.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To present online:
        li Select the Slide Show tab, then locate the Start Slide Show group.
        li Click the Present Online command.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/advance/advance15.jpg")
        li  A dialog box will appear. Click Connect. A status message will appear as PowerPoint prepares your online presentation.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/advance/advance16.png")
        li A link will appear. If it's not already selected, select the link.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Click Copy Link to make a copy of the link or Send in Email to send an email with the link to your viewers.
        li Click Start Presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance17.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Present the slide show as you normally would, using the mouse or keyboard to advance the slides.
        li When you are finished, click End Online Presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance18.jpg")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li A dialog box will appear to confirm that you wish to end the presentation. Click End Online Presentation.
        img(src="images/advance/advance19.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Customizing your slide show
        li Sometimes you might want to hide a slide while still keeping it in your presentation. For instance, if you are presenting a slide show to more than one group of people, hiding or even rearranging certain slides could help you tailor your slide show to each group you present it to. You could also choose to create a shortened version of your slide show to present when you're short on time. The Custom Slide Show feature allows you to create and name different versions of your slide show with hidden or rearranged slides.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To create a custom show:
        li Select the Slide Show tab, then locate the Start Slide Show group.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Click the Custom Slide Show command, then select Custom Shows.
        img(src="images/advance/advance20.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li A dialog box will appear. Click New. 
        img(src="images/advance/advance21.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li The Define Custom Show dialog box will appear. Locate the Slide show name field, and type in a name for your custom show.
        li In the Slides in presentation: area, check the box next to the slides you would like to include in your custom show.
        li Click Add to add the slides to the Slides in custom show: box. If necessary, use the up and down arrows to reorder the added slides.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/advance/advance22.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Click OK.
        li Select Close to exit or Show to view your custom show.
        img(src="images/advance/advance23.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li To play the custom show at any time, click the Custom Slide Show command, then select the desired presentation from the drop-down menu.
        img(src="images/advance/advance24.png")


